<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: THOUSAND OAKS; 
</P>
<P>
HEARING PLANNED ON CONTRACT PROPOSAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEPHANIE STASSEL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A public hearing on a contract proposal by a union representing 600 Conejo 
Valley Unified School District employees is scheduled Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
The California School Employees Assn., representing classified workers, has 
proposed a 30% raise over the next three years, plus 15% of the district's 
lottery money each year. 
</P>
<P>
For the first time since 1985, the union's proposal would give the workers a 
flat percentage raise, instead of basing their raises on the state funding 
received by the district. 
</P>
<P>
Area residents will be able to comment on the proposal at the hearing, 
scheduled for 7:30 p.m. at Westlake High School. 
</P>
<P>
District officials said they will present their offer at the school board's 
Nov. 8 meeting. A second public hearing, to discuss the district's position, is 
planned for Nov. 20. 
</P>
<P>
Negotiations on the contract, which expires Dec. 31, are expected to begin in 
early December, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
For three years, classified employees -- including secretaries, custodians, 
maintenance and food service workers -- received raises ranging from 2.88% to 
4.59%, plus 8% of the district's lottery funds. STEPHANIE STASSEL 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA102490-0009 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 296832 </DOCID>
