<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN YSIDRO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Agents seized more than 200 pounds of marijuana and arrested two men near the 
border checkpoint, the Border Patrol reported Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Dagoberto Meza-Hernandez, 24, of Tijuana, and Bernardo Vasquez-Guvioto, 28, of 
Sinaloa, Mexico, were booked into the Metropolitan Correctional Center on drug 
possession charges, said a Border Patrol spokesman, adding that both men were 
in the United States illegally. 
</P>
<P>
Agents arrested the two at about 5:30 p.m. Monday as they allegedly were 
loading 218 pounds of marijuana into a 1984 Ford Bronco on Monument Road, about 
half a mile north of the U.S.-Mexican border, the spokesman said. The marijuana 
was packaged in three duffel bags and two backpacks and agents believe the 
drugs were carried across the border on foot and were going to be driven north 
in the Bronco, the spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Three other men fled on foot back into Mexico. 
</P>
</TEXT>
