<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Allergan Inc.: The international maker of contact lenses and eye- and skin-care 
products posted third-quarter income of $25.4 million, 14% less than a year 
ago. 
</P>
<P>
Allergan Inc., formerly a unit of SmithKline Beckman Corp., went public July 
27, 1989. Sales advanced 8% to a record $222.2 million. The Irvine firm said 
the results resulted from strong sales growth in its pharmaceutical, surgical 
and dermatology businesses, which came despite adverse sales in optical 
operations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
