<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
From the Battlefield to the Diamond: Ken Burns, producer, director and writer 
of the acclaimed PBS series, "The Civil War," will team up again with General 
Motors, the sole corporate underwriter of the highly-rated series, for a 
five-hour film history of America's national pastime entitled "Baseball." The 
program, now being researched, is scheduled to air on PBS in 1993. CLAUDIA PUIG 
</P>
</TEXT>
