<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Soon to Be Back in the Saddle: Roy Rogers, "the king of the cowboys," is 
recovering from surgery to correct an aneurysm near his heart. 
</P>
<P>
The singing cowboy movie and television star, who will be 79 on Nov. 5, had the 
operation Monday at a hospital in Apple Valley, and was doing fine after the 
surgery, his son Roy Jr. said. Rogers underwent triple-bypass surgery 13 years 
ago. Riding a golden palomino named Trigger and strumming on a guitar, Rogers 
rode off into the sunsets of some 90 musical Westerns in a career that spanned 
more than 30 years. CLAUDIA PUIG 
</P>
</TEXT>
