<HEADLINE>
<P>
LANCERS WIN SHOWDOWN WITH ROYAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS PARKER, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As the Thousand Oaks High girls' volleyball team broke from its huddle before 
the third game of Tuesday night's Marmonte League showdown at Royal, the 
players shook with emotion. 
</P>
<P>
Were the Lancers nervous because they trailed, two games to none? No, actually, 
they were feeling a bit giggly. 
</P>
<P>
"We went out (onto the court) laughing," outside hitter Aimee Stone said. "We 
do so much better when we're having fun." 
</P>
<P>
Laughter turned out to be the Lancers' best medicine. Thousand Oaks, ranked 
fifth in the Southern Section 5-A Division, took the next three games to win 
the match, 15-17, 8-15, 15-9, 15-2, 15-11. 
</P>
<P>
Royal, ranked 10th in the 5-A Division, took a 7-1 lead in the fifth game 
before Thousand Oaks (14-1, 11-0 in league play) made its second serve. 
</P>
<P>
The Highlanders (11-2, 9-2) served with an 11-9 lead, but Erikka Gulbranson's 
spike forced a sideout. 
</P>
<P>
Gulbranson sandwiched two of her game-high five aces around a Cindy McKinnon 
kill to give Thousand Oaks a 12-11 lead. A Royal error and two more McKinnon 
kills gave Thousand Oaks the match. 
</P>
<P>
Kaili Kimura and Gulbranson each had 17 kills and Stone added 16 for Thousand 
Oaks. Royal's Wende Brown had a match-high 20 kills. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Thousand Oaks' Jenny Streltzoff (12) watches a dink by Royal's Wende 
Brown, left, clear the net in a Marmonte League match Tuesday night. GEORGE 
WILHELM / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
