<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
RTD LAUDS FREE-RIDE PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles Rapid Transit District's free-ride pilot program to patrons 
whose buses are at least 15 minutes late was a "phenomenal" success in its 
first month, with ridership increasing by about 1 million over the same period 
last year, officials announced today. 
</P>
<P>
Of the nearly 34 million passengers who rode RTD buses in September, about 
59,000 -- or 0.18% of the total -- qualified for free rides under the agency's 
warranty program, far less than the 600,000 officials had predicted. 
</P>
<P>
"This is a phenomenal RTD success story," board President Nick Patsaouras said 
at a downtown news conference, adding that he will recommend that the program 
be permanently implemented beyond its scheduled December expiration if the 
success continues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
