<HEADLINE>
<P>
P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
'RACIST' BILLBOARDS STIR AUSTRALIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SYDNEY, Australia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Advertising billboards blasted as racist have brewed up a storm in Australia, 
where South African anti-apartheid leader Nelson Mandela is visiting. 
</P>
<P>
Hahn Brewing Co. said today it would consider withdrawing its advertisements 
after complaints that they are racist and ridicule black people. 
</P>
<P>
The advertisement urges drinkers to "Get Your Laughing Gear Around This." One 
depicts a black person with an elongated neck adorned with rings, while another 
shows a wide-eyed black man balancing a bottle of beer on his lip. 
</P>
<P>
"Imagine Nelson Mandela's reaction, coming to Sydney and seeing ads like that," 
a New South Wales state politician said. 
</P>
<P>
Hahn Managing Director Chuck Hahn said the advertisements, which were approved 
by state advertising authorities, are making a humorous comment about the beer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
