<P>
MD-11 SETS RECORD TO KOREA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONG BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Douglas Aircraft Co.'s new MD-11 commercial jetliner set a speed record during 
a test flight from Dallas to the South Korean capital of Seoul, the company 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The three-engine jet covered 7,266 miles without stopping in 14 hours and 50 
minutes on Tuesday, the company said. 
</P>
<P>
The record was set as part of the MD-11's certification flight test program 
with the Federal Aviation Administration. 
</P>
<P>
Douglas said it had applied to register the flight as a point-to-point speed 
record with the International Federation of Aeronautics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
