<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
MOTHER DIES CHEERING HER SON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MONTICELLO, Ill. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A woman died of heart failure after choking on candy while cheering her son 
during a high school football game. 
</P>
<P>
Shawn Overocker, a tight end at St. Theresa High School, caught his first pass 
of the year during Monday night's junior varsity game against Monticello. 
</P>
<P>
But when Candace Overocker began cheering, she choked on some hard candy, said 
William Mundt, Piatt County medical examiner. 
</P>
<P>
"Within two minutes, she was given CPR" by paramedics attending the game, Mundt 
said. And crowd members tried the Heimlich maneuver, a squeeze that can 
dislodge an object from the throat of a choking victim. 
</P>
<P>
But Mrs. Overocker, 35, of Decatur was pronounced dead at Kirby Hospital in 
Monticello. 
</P>
